#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.86"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.86:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.86:0.2"
msgid "9. Channavagga "
msgstr "9. With Channa "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 86. Saṅkhittadhammasutta → saṅkhitta (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.86:0.3"
msgid "86. Saṅkhittadhammasutta "
msgstr "86. A Teaching In Brief "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn35.86:1.1"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Seated to one side, Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.86:1.2"
msgid "“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṃkhittena dhammaṃ desetu, yamahaṃ bhagavato dhammaṃ sutvā eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto vihareyyan”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief. When I’ve heard it, I’ll live alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.86:2.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, ānanda, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Ānanda? "

msgctxt "sn35.86:2.2"
msgid "cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is the eye permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn35.86:3.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.86:4.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn35.86:5.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn35.86:6.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn35.86:6.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn35.86:7.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn35.86:8.1"
msgid "“Rūpā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti? "
msgstr "“Are sights … "

#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn35.86:9.1"
msgid "“Aniccā, bhante” … pe …. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.55, sc10
msgctxt "sn35.86:10.1"
msgid "“Cakkhuviññāṇaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "eye consciousness … eye contact … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.86:10.2"
msgid "yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "The pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact: is that permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn35.86:11.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn35.86:12.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn35.86:13.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn35.86:14.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn35.86:14.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "sn35.86:15.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante” … pe …. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "sn35.86:16.1"
msgid "“Jivhā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti? "
msgstr "“Is the ear … nose … tongue … body … mind … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "sn35.86:17.1"
msgid "“Aniccā, bhante” … pe …. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "sn35.86:18.1"
msgid "“Jivhāviññāṇaṃ … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.86:18.2"
msgid "jivhāsamphasso … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.86:18.3"
msgid "yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "The pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact: is that permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "sn35.86:19.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "sn35.86:20.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "sn35.86:21.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "sn35.86:22.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn35.86:22.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "sn35.86:23.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24
msgctxt "sn35.86:24.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ passaṃ, ānanda, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati … pe … cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati … pe … "
msgstr "“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact. And they grow disillusioned with the painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.86:24.2"
msgid "yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati. "
msgstr "They grow disillusioned with the ear … nose … tongue … body … mind … painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.86:24.3"
msgid "Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.86:24.4"
msgid "‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.86:24.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

